<br>
Speaking of boots ... we talked a bit about the dwarven culturals last night, and I wanted to extend the offer of my hammer and forge to your fashion needs. Outside of the lava rocks, mercury and leather paddings (that must be hunted up), all of the rest of the materials (from the Brellium to the rubies) is to be hand in Kaladim. And if you're willing to bring along a fine enchanter (level 49+) and buy them a copy of Enchant Brellium from the library in Ak'Anon (so that they can enchant the metal -- a 60 enchanter can't quite enchant the ore for one breastplate attempt on a full mana bar), I'm more than happy to smith the items for you for the cost of the materials there. Even though these items aren't trivial for me yet, I'm currently averaging a 85% percent success rate on the armor, so the following "costs" below really represent no failures along the way (so you might plan for a 20% "buffer" for failures.)<br>
<br>
Still, the value of many of the items that come from the forge are particularly suited to our line of work: armor class, strength, stamina, wisdom and resists. Do let me know if I can make you anything, I tend to smith on the weekends (unless my orders get backed up) earlier in the day.<br>
<br>
